The talks broke up at around 5:30 am local time. JOHANNESBURG - Political parties in Democratic Republic of Congo paused talks on Saturday close to a deal under which President Joseph Kabila would leave power in 2017 and elections would be held the same year, participants at the talks said.The talks broke up at around 5:30am local time after about 12 hours of non-stop negotiations and were set to reconvene at 11 am, participants said.